.TH PAW-PROXY 1 "2026-02" "paw-proxy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
paw-proxy \- Zero\-config HTTPS proxy for local macOS development
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B paw-proxy
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B paw-proxy
Zero\-config HTTPS proxy for local macOS development.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Configure DNS, CA, and install daemon (requires sudo) Requires sudo.
.TP
.B uninstall
Remove all paw\-proxy components
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-brew
Skip CA removal prompt (used by Homebrew uninstall hook)
.RE
.TP
.B status
Show daemon status and registered routes
.TP
.B run
Run daemon in foreground (used by launchd)
.TP
.B logs
Show daemon logs
.RS
.TP
.B \-f , \-\-tail
Follow log output in real time
.RE
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Truncate the log file
.RE
.TP
.B doctor
Run diagnostics to check system health
.TP
.B version
Show version
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Initial setup (creates CA, configures DNS, installs daemon):
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ sudo paw\-proxy setup
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check if daemon is running and see active routes:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ paw\-proxy status
.fi
.RE
.PP
Follow daemon logs in real time:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ paw\-proxy logs \-f
.fi
.RE
.PP
Diagnose common issues:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ paw\-proxy doctor
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/paw\-proxy/
Support directory (CA, socket, config)
.TP
.I ~/Library/Logs/paw\-proxy.log
Daemon log file
.TP
.I /etc/resolver/test
macOS DNS resolver for .test TLD
.TP
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.alexcatdad.paw\-proxy.plist
LaunchAgent for auto\-start
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR up(1)
